        public StateValues doSteadyState(java.io.File initDistFile)

      • doSteadyState

        public StateValues doSteadyState(StateValues initDist)
                          throws PrismException
        Compute steady-state probability distribution (forwards). Optionally, use the passed in vector initDist as the initial probability distribution (time 0). If null, start from initial state (or uniform distribution over multiple initial states). For reasons of efficiency, when a vector is passed in, it will be trampled over and then deleted afterwards, so if you wanted it, take a copy.
        Throws:
        PrismException

      • computeRestrictedNext

        protected StateValues computeRestrictedNext(JDDNode tr,
                                            JDDNode a,
                                            StateValues x)
        Given a value vector x, compute the probability: v(s) = Sum_s' P(s,s')*x(s') for s labeled with a, v(s) = 0 for s not labeled with a. Clears the StateValues object x.
        Parameters:
        tr - the transition matrix
        a - the set of states labeled with a
        x - the value vector

      • computeSteadyStateProbs

        public StateValues computeSteadyStateProbs(JDDNode tr,
                                           StateValues initDist)
                                    throws PrismException
        Compute steady-state probability distribution (forwards). Use the passed in vector initDist as the initial probability distribution (time 0). The type of this should match the current engine (i.e. StateValuesMTBDD for MTBDD, StateValuesDV for sparse/hybrid). For reasons of efficiency, this vector will be trampled over and then deleted afterwards, so if you wanted it, take a copy.
        Parameters:
        tr - The transition probability matrix for the DTMC
        initDist - Initial distribution (will be overwritten)
        Throws:
        PrismException

      • computeSteadyStateProbsForBSCC

        protected StateValues computeSteadyStateProbsForBSCC(JDDNode tr,
                                                     JDDNode bscc)
                                              throws PrismException
        Compute steady-state probabilities for a BSCC i.e. compute the long-run probability of being in each state of the BSCC. No initial distribution is specified since it does not affect the result. The result will be stored in a full vector whose size equals the number of states in the DTMC.
        Parameters:
        tr - The transition probability matrix for the whole DTMC
        bscc - The BSCC to be analysed
        Throws:
        PrismException

      • computeTransientProbs

        protected StateValues computeTransientProbs(JDDNode tr,
                                            StateValues initDist,
                                            int time)
                                     throws PrismException
        Compute transient probability distribution (forwards). Use the passed in vector initDist as the initial probability distribution (time 0). The type of this should match the current engine (i.e. StateValuesMTBDD for MTBDD, StateValuesDV for sparse/hybrid). For reasons of efficiency, this vector will be trampled over and then deleted afterwards, so if you wanted it, take a copy.
        Parameters:
        tr - The transition probability matrix for the DTMC
        initDist - Initial distribution (will be overwritten)
        time - Time step
        Throws:
        PrismException
